Buyer beware. They have had a lot of turnover during the pandemic and signage from OSHA on the windows implies they weren’t following COVID precautions. Customer service has taken a turn for the worse, and when you are forced to stand outside in 90+ degree weather (no social distancing markers) for a sandwich you ordered online an hour prior (when the wait time online said 20 minutes) and the manager obviously couldn’t care less...it’s time to take your business elsewhere. What was once a family friendly place now just seems to be a money making machine. $15 for a meatball sandwich that has THREE meatballs?! Cmon....

We normally have a great experience here. Maybe they’re a little short staffed or having a huge rush of orders today. But I called to place an order, she said she was putting me on hold and instead she hung up me. I called back to hear a voicemail that says “due to covid they’re only accepting orders online”. The girl on the phone could have just said that to me before she accidentally hung up on me, but I’m glad to hear that information either way. I ordered online. Then, I picked up my order from the window and it was ready 10 minutes before they estimated. I was pleasantly surprised. But when I got home, I found that they forgot my sandwich. Tried to call to let them know they forgot it, and they didn’t answer. Went back to pick the sandwich up and the girl at the window seemed like she just didn’t want to be there today. Sandwich had wilted lettuce and seemed like it had been sitting out for a bit. Meatballs and soup were room temp - Subpar. Weird vibe today.

Love this place. 5 stars every time. Get the B Franklin

I have been eating sandwiches from Tempesta for years. They are consistently some of the best I've ever had. I think it is a result of creative recipes and top quality ingredients that make these so fantastic. I highly recommend them. The food is not that cheap, but well worth the price for what you get.

I have not visited this place for about a year. Few days ago I stopped by and I have to say that I was very disappointed with what I’ve ordered.My favorite sandwich ( #7) was not the same at all. Unfortunately this time it was nothing like that.

First off... No. Not related to the business at all. Happen to share the same name and made it a point to visit before I headed out of Chicago today.  Simply put it was awesome to have my name represented so well!  Fantastic deli style casual, amazing meats on display and on sandwiches. Got the Dante and a pastry. The Dante was absolutely delectable with meats and cheese stuffed into a delicious piece of fresh bread. The pastry was awesome. The staff were super friendly and supposedly I'm the 3rd Tempesta to make the pilgrimage. Hahaha  This is the type of place I wish I had in Vegas. But I don't. I'll make it a point to visit every time I enter Chi-Town.

today was my first of many visits to Tempesta! i ordered the B.Franklin turkey sandwich on toasted sour dough bread it was out of this world!!!  i loved the bread so much i bought a half loave to go! then i ordered a small latte it arrived at same time as my sandwich!! The sandwich come with chips or fruit , i picked a apricot! I was expecting a little mini cup but no not here..i got the whole fruit! now to finish off my lunch i got a gelato it was so rich but so good! everyone was nice and friendly i felt right at home on my first visit! will i be back??????????????? your darn tooting i will!!! plus its very close to work in West Town!

We got the charcuterie board with three meats and three cheeses, salad, spaghetti and meatballs, and the bolognese. Everything was delicious, but the charcuterie board took the show. Probably the best I've had in the city. On top of the great food, it was some of the best service I've ever had. I would go back just for the service. Thank you Tempesta for the great experience!!

Everything I've had has been excellent (salads, soups, chicken sandwich). 💯  Only wish they offered earlier delivery on Caviar so I can eat it sooner!

The muffulletta is insane. It's the best sandwich I've ever had. Now I have to go back and try some of the others. But I don't  know if I will be able to resist just getting that incredible sandwich again. I would drive across the city for that sandwich. It's outrageously delicious- they also have nitrate free meats (if relevant for you; it's a dealbreaker for me). Sandwiches come with a choice of fruit or chips- both are good.  They sell deli meats and cheeses amongst other products and have a small pasta menu to order from- everything smelled amazing. Nice, small patio- on this stretch of Grand it is nice and quiet. Tempesta is a fun market with a very friendly staff- who are helpful and very chill.  That muffulletta though- I had to wait a few minutes to process how delicious it was after taking the first bite. It may be a special or just off-menu; but in true fashion was pre-assembled and sitting on the counter ready to go. I hate to say it- but it crushes the muffulletta at Central Grocery in NOLA (sorry) but in the best way. And I love Central Grocery. This was like a discovery of flavor and texture, messy and all of the best qualities a Chicagoan could want on a sandwich- silky, thin deli meats, the most perfect amount of sogginess and picked vegetables and olives falling everywhere.  The gelato is good too- I ordered pistachio and it was heavenly. I accidentally ordered a small and should have gotten the kid's as I did not read the size amount.  I can't wait to go back!

The nduja arancini is fantastic and the chicken with mashed potatoes and pan sauce on the dinner menu is without a doubt the best I've ever had.   The wine is nicely priced and the atmosphere is great.  The staff is friendly and attentive.  The place is family owned and there has been a lot of thought put into everything that is fine there.  It definitely shows.  The sandwiches are great, the dinner menu is great, the drinks are great, the gelato is great, the people are great.   What's not to love?

Finally got in The Tempesta Deli. Tried the Zeppo meatball sandwich. 3 smaller well made meatballs but small on a highly buttered texas toast bread. Bread very soft but surprisingly held sandwich together. If there was cheese it had little or no impact could hardly taste it. I expected a whole lot more for $13.23. Go to Nonna's on Randolph u get a much larger sandwich for less $$ and the bread is far superior.

To die for.  Get the Dante sandwich.  You won't have to eat for 24 hours.  After the 1st bite, you won't share it with anyone because it is THAT good. Still hungry? There's plenty of equally delicious gelato.

OMG! I got the # 34 – The Potato’ Nator and it was fabulous! I got my egg over hard because I don't like runny egg yolk...and man it was fantastic! My sandwich was so hot and fresh! I could tell they actually cook my order after I ordered it and not an hour before , and then just placed it under a heat lamp. Everything from the brioche bun to the bacon to the egg to the hashbrown was flavorful.  I opted to not get the pickled red onions, and if I had known they were going to put some kind of aoli sauce on it. I probably would have omitted that as well. Be aware of the "Tabasco sauce"! They put that directly on the egg instead of the brioche bun. I'm from Texas so I don't mind a little spicy kick in the mouth every once in a while. Now, lets move on to the OUTSTANDING , homemade, melt in your mouth, chocolate chip cookies for $3.00. They were soooooo good! The cookie was crunchy on the outside and chewy on the inside. The chocolate chips weren't overly sweet, so it was the perfect ending to a great lunch. I will definitely be back!

This review is only biased on service for Saturday PM Dec 1. The food here is excellent. I walked in, grabbed some water and headed over to the counter. The woman at the counter ignored me grabbed her phone and walked into the bathroom with the towel she uses to clean the counters. There were three other employees working none of which even said hello all stood with their backs to the customer. One lady that was closest to the counter was making a coffee drink. She saw me out of the corner of her eye but tried not to make any contact. I stood at the counter waiting to place my order for about 5-7minutes until the lady finished the coffee drink walked it over to the guy who ordered it and then proceeded to clean the coffee machine...all the while leaving me standing there without even saying Hi. On top of the fact that there were two other employees circling around doing everything else but acknowledging the customer. She finished her VERY long and drawn out cleaning of the espresso machine turns around very annoyed and says "what would you like?" Her attitude couldn't of been more I don't care. I ordered my sandwich and sat at a table to wait for my food. Just then the lady who was at the register (the one who walked away with her cell phone when I walked in) walked out of the bathroom with the same towel she wipes the counters down with and tucked it back through her belt loop (GROSS). Bottom line my experience sucked and the customer service here really needs to improve. There needs to be an employee meeting him how you treat your guests as well as sanitary standards.

You're not gonna find a better sandwich shop than Tempesta in West Town.  Streetside parking is hit or miss; you might have to park up to 1 or 2 blocks away. There are some free spots and some paid spots available. Close to a bus stop (Grand & Noble), there are bike racks nearby.  The sandwich choices are awesome; very creative and quality ingredients. Tempesta sources some of their meat from Green Grocer and cures their meat in-house. I don't know where they get their bread but it is delicious.  It smells great in the deli, there are a couple tables and a ledge by the window with high chairs. There are usually some scents of coffee / espresso blended in with the other various deli aromas.  They use those rectangular aluminum containers for carryout, in a study paper bag. Plastic utensils.  I've ordered in shop and also via the ritual app. Great experience both times. If you want a chicken sandwich, try The Roost Carolina Kitchen. Everything is else is amazing. Updated Nov 2018.

Decided to try Tempesta Market after reading online reviews from others  It's a small place and the outside is unobtrusive and easy to overlook.  An Italian Deli, an in-house charcuterie, gelate, with a wonderful selection of interesting craft sandwiches, and an array of gourmet pantry items to take home.  We had the Southside Johnny $13 (Porchetta, Brun-uusto, Broccolini, Chimichurri, Cheese, Pickled Fennel with Rosemary Broth on Sourdough) and the B. Franklin $11(Roasted Turkey, Hooks 2-Year Cheddar, Pickled Fresno, Avocado, Pea Shoots, Sofrito Aioli on Sourdough, I added Bacon for and additional $2).  The Southside Johnny is a hot sandwich and I loved the mixture of ingredients, it tasted great!  The B. Franklin is a cold sandwich and just perfect for a hot summer day, All ingredients were fresh and delicious!  We went here for lunch on a weekday, it was busy, but not overly crowded.  I'll bet they are really crowded on the weekends.  There are 4 large communal type wooden tables and benches to sit at or you can take your order to go.  There is street parking only, and it can be hard to find at times.  Try the gelato, we tried the pistachio and it was really delicious!  My only disappointment was that they did not bring out the muffaleta's until we were leaving. they are not on the menu and they sell out quickly.  If you do not see them on top of the middle case, ask if they are available, that's what i am going to get next time I return.
Awesome experience, amazing food. I recommend the food, small grocery selection is nice too.

Excellent. Had the B Franklin, meatballs and chocolate chip cookie. Will be back.

It was so hard to make a decision, every damn sandwich looked like a work of art. Can’t wait to go back and try more. Thanks for curing my hangover with your hashbrown breakfast sammie and Orange gelato. Staff was incredibly friendly and helpful, thanks Marcus!
First time at Tempesta and I ordered the Potato-Nator by recommendation of friend of mine. The sandwich blew me away. The gentleman that took our order was very helpful and polite.

Love it.  Started talking shop about growing food and cooking.  Dude went in the back and gave me a half pint of his grandpas ground chilies from calabria, told me to grow them, they’re sprouting. Good joint. GREAT food.
Best sandwich I've ever had.

Are you kidding me or what? Every item here is another level.  Words cannot describe the flavors of deliciousness that you will experience. Some nights I dream about their foccatia bread others I dream about the rice crispy treats. Service is always on point and they have the best cookies.......... in the world!
Fantastic. Tried the Potato' Nator and the Beet Sandwichs. Both were very good.

Fantastic rustic interior with delicious bites (spreadable salami, olives, soup) and friendly staff. Perfect place for a bite or to grab goodies for the ultimate charcuterie.
Spreadable salami is amazing!  Great spot for carnivores!

We stumbled on this place totally by accident on our way to another sandwich shop down the street and oh my gosh I am so glad we did. I give this place 5 stars for the following points: - Design/Ambiance: Great, the interior is comfortable and there is a deli counter and a cool assortment of Italian groceries/condiments/pasta etc. - Service: Great, everyone who was working was knowledgeable and friendly - Food: EXCELLENT. I was expecting a decent sandwich, but wow this was unlike any that I have had in a while. Flavors were unique and went well together, was a hearty portion but not too much. Very happy. Ultimately I think this place fills a void; A super high quality, delicious, and casual sandwich place where you can go and leave happy for under $20. What more do you want?

Plenty of space for a deli if you wanted to set up a laptop and get some work done which is nice. To top it all off, they have handmade gelato. What more could you ask for?!  Very friendly staff. I’ll definitely be back.

The best gourmet sandwiches in Chicago period! This custom little shop is putting out a line of cured meats that you will not find anywhere else. Do yourself a favor and stop in for a sandwich and leave with some nduja.

We've tried a lot already and have given everything two thumbs up - lunch sandwiches and salads, to-go sauce and their homemade pasta (which is a steal!), cured meats, espresso and even the strangely-awesome fried rosemary rice krispie treats! It also doesn't hurt that everyone working there is super helpful, friendly and LOVES food.

Loved, and I mean loved the food! Service was a bit spotty. :(  Left without getting gelato due to a lack of basic attention paid by counter folks which was disappointing. Too much occupying themselves with clean up, etc. and explaining what they had to offer. Not enough basic understanding how to supply good service. Coming back to try it one more time because that gelato looked absolutely amazing and I believe they may grow into their roles. Fingers crossed.
is pretty pricey but the owner is super nice. meats, gelato are all excellent.
Spotless clean place and the best cured meats I have ever had in Chicago. Friendly and helpful staff. Great neighborhood market!
Very friendly staff. Great quality food. We will be going back for lunch.
Unbelievable subs. Great addition to the neighborhood!
Incredible. Amazing selection of cheeses and charcuterie and sandwiches and more. So happy a place like this opened up in my neighborhood. Plus they have gelato, folks. Just go.

Wow. Tried their takeout for the first time last night, absolutely amazing spot. Food was 10/10, absolutely recommend. Will be coming back for sure. Had the B. Franklin, Qx2, and the meatball appetizer, each one was better than the next. Good portions and fair price for the quality.

Thrilled to have this addition to the neighborhood.  There's a lot of meat and cheese options to make your own charcuterie board including olives and other sides.  They're also making sandwiches and salads to order and have gelato in house.  With 4 pork-free meats already available and a quick chat with the owner revealed some more options on the way, I'm definitely coming back.
The food was phenomenal and filling. I 100% recommend this new establishment.

The employees are very knowledgeable and friendly. The selection of meats and cheeses is fantastic considering the size of the place. The ‘Nduja is A+++ and the soda selection is ridiculous. Can’t wait to go back already.
Incredible first day! Solid meats and sandwiches, and Kuri Kuri soup was delicious. All good! Charcuterie board was insane...! Pâtés were super fresh, and texture was spot on.

We went here tonight on their 1st night open. We drove all the way up from Hyde Park because we LOVE cured meats, especially Nduja.  We could not have been more pleased with our experience. There is a giant log of Nduja split open on the counter above their selection of meats and cheeses.  You can sample it. (which of course we did!) They have fantastic gelato, and also some light produce options (e.g., eggs). Locally made Kombucha. But the stars of the show are their cheeses and most definitely their meats!  We ordered the 6 meats and 2 cheeses (chef's choice).  EVERYTHING WAS AMAZING. Very full flavored meats, several spicy options which we loved.   All I can say is that we've been looking for  years for a great charcuterie and cheese board and have finally found it. Skip purple pig, tete charcuterie, and even Old Town Social and go here.  You will not find a higher quality, friendlier neighborhood spot.   Thanks for being worth the drive, we'll definitely be back!
The best damn Porchetta Sandwich and Calabrian Salumi I’ve EVER had! You have to try it, it’s insane!!

I was walking by and the storefront immediately caught my attention. The owner invited me in and gave me a tour of the kitchen and meat curing process. Very cool market and friendly employees. Handmade pasta! The food looks delicious and can’t wait for it to open tomorrow

From the moment I walked in, The fresh smell of Authenticity struck me like a bolt of lightning.  I could almost taste the air. From their fresh full service Delicatessen, to their in house charcuterie.  Soda's I have never seen before with flavor beyond belief.  Fresh made Sandwiches that would impress the Enthusiast in you.  Don't leave without a scoop of Gelato "to go" and some Specialty pantry items to bring "Italy" home.  I couldn't ask for a better experience. Hats off to Mr. Tony Fiasche and his team. I will be back for more!
